# Component Design

## Rules
- Component style: {{COMPONENT_STYLE}} (e.g. function components, not class).
- Split presentational vs container per {{COMPONENT_SPLIT}}.
- One component, one responsibility; split when too large.
- Props are clearly typed; avoid deep prop-drilling (use state management if needed).

## Structure
- Component folder organization: {{COMPONENT_FOLDER}}.
- Styling: {{STYLING_APPROACH}}.
- Component library: {{COMPONENT_LIBRARY}}.
<!-- COMPONENT_LIBRARY: e.g. "shadcn/ui (Radix primitives + Tailwind)". When set, prefer existing library components; do NOT hand-build primitives the library already provides. With shadcn, install/inspect components via the shadcn MCP (see ../.claude/rules/tooling.md). Drop this line if the project has no component library. -->

## Adding a shadcn component
<!-- Drop this whole section if the project does not use shadcn/ui. -->
- Use the shadcn MCP (or `npx shadcn@latest add <name>`) to add a component, then adapt it — do NOT copy-paste an ad-hoc reimplementation.
